PARAM.name: cequinox
PARAM.DESCRIPTION: Equinox of the image world coordinate system (WCS).

PARAM.name: ctype
PARAM.DESCRIPTION: Orthographic Projection. The first image axis represents right ascension and the second represents declination.

PARAM.name: bunit
PARAM.DESCRIPTION: The units used to represent bandpass values.

FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Concise description of the image returned.
Image access reference URL.
ICRS right-ascension of the image center.
ICRS declination of the image center.
Number of Image Axes.
An array giving the length in pixels of each image axis.
An array giving the scale in degrees per pixel of each image axis.
MIME-type of the object pointed to by the image access reference URL.
An array specifying the image pixel coordinates of the WCS reference pixel.
An array specifying the world coordinates of the WCS reference pixel.
Twist in degrees about Image Center, +AXIS2 West of North (J2000)
2MASS Image Band
The reference wavelength of the 2MASS Image Filter.
Upper wavelength limit of the 2MASS Image Filter.
Lower wavelength limit of the 2MASS Image Filter.
Type of Image (Q=Quicklook; A=Atlas)
The 2MASS dataset the image belongs to.
Pixel flags of source image
An identifier for the search constraint the FITS Image was found/retrieved for

This field will contain null values unless the meta-data table is the result of a query involving a list of constraints (positions, coadd_keys, or DHSs). When non-null, the value of this column is an integer identifier for the search constraint the FITS Image was found/retrieved for.
The reference date of the FITS image, in yymmdd format (yy: last 2 digits of the observation year, mm: integer month, dd: integer day). This can differ by one day from the actual UT observation date.
The hemisphere of the 2MASS observatory where the FITS image was taken. There are only two possible values: 'n' = north (Mt. Hopkins), and 's' = south (Cerro Tololo).
The nightly scan number of the FITS image.
The image number of the FITS image.
UT when the FITS image was taken, in yymmdd format (yy: last 2 digits of the observation year, mm: integer month, dd: integer day).

The coadd_key value of the FITS image. This is a unique identifier for the observation date, observatory hemisphere, nightly scan number, and image number of the FITS image. Each source in the 2MASS All-Sky Point and Extended Source Catalogs is tagged with a coadd_key value identifying the 2MASS Image Set it was extracted from.
Seeing Full Width Half Maximum (in arcseconds)
Photometric zero-point magnitude of the FITS image.
Approximate SNR=10 magnitude of the FITS image.
The ID of the HTM triangle (subdivision level 7) containing the FITS image reference location.
The right ascension (in degrees, J2000) of the search position the FITS image was returned for
The declination (in degrees, J2000) of the search position the FITS image was returned for
The subimage/cutout size (in arcseconds) requested around the search position
